LAST DEPLOYED: Mon Feb  9 16:53:45 2026
NAMESPACE: infra-services
STATUS: deployed
REVISION: 1
DESCRIPTION: Install complete
NOTES:
kube-prometheus-stack has been installed. Check its status by running:
  kubectl --namespace infra-services get pods -l "release=prometheus"

Get Grafana 'admin' user password by running:

  kubectl --namespace infra-services get secrets prometheus-grafana -o jsonpath="{.data.admin-password}" | base64 -d ; echo
  >> sEvQVHxcOCB0DmIkaMxWvSGRLXFVzJYEXHlmRvHD
Access Grafana local instance:

  export POD_NAME=$(kubectl --namespace infra-services get pod -l "app.kubernetes.io/name=grafana,app.kubernetes.io/instance=prometheus" -oname)
  kubectl --namespace infra-services port-forward $POD_NAME 3000

kubectl port-forward service/prometheus-grafana 3000:80 -n infra-services
Get your grafana admin user password by running:

  kubectl get secret --namespace infra-services -l app.kubernetes.io/component=admin-secret -o jsonpath="{.items[0].data.admin-password}" | base64 --decode ; echo


Visit https://github.com/prometheus-operator/kube-prometheus for instructions on how to create & configure Alertmanager and Prometheus instances using the Operator.